Experts from Centre for International Research in the Humanities and Social Sciences in New York City studied neolithic ornaments to understand how farming spread . 
  Northern Europeans in the Neolithic period initially rejected the practice of farming . 
  Their findings show a bump in the road in the adoption of farming which enabled groups of people to move away from foraging and hunting . 
  The first farmers came to Europe 8,000 years ago and spread agricultural practices in Greece . 
 